px\"},\"insert\":\"Empire State of the South\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\".\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"Georgia has shed its image as a largely agricultural state it had in the 19th century and is home to the headquarters of several major corporations as well as the busiest airport in the world, \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Heartsfield_Jackson_international_airport\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"Heartsfield Jackson international airport\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\" in Atlanta. While most people thinking of Georgia immediately think of Atlanta, there is still a lot the rural Georgia of yore left and Southern hospitality has lost nothing of its charm and is - contrary to common prejudices - more often than not extended to people of all origins and creeds.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-QNN9Vkv_yzQ/T__Nr3pFV0I/AAAAAAAACn4/ap0-j6EGvGo/s1600/promenade_mall_fountain_forsyth_park_savannah_georgia_usa_20120713.jpg\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"}]}"
