west_virginia_body = "{\"ops\":[{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"http://westvirginia.com/\",\"bold\":true,\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\"},\"insert\":\"West Virginia\"},{\"insert\":\" is a state in the \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/South_(United_States_of_America)\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Southern Region\"},{\"insert\":\" of the \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/United_States_of_America\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"United States of America\"},{\"insert\":\". It's often called the \\\"Mountain State\\\", being the only state in the USA to lie completely within a mountain range (in this case, the \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Appalachian_Mountains\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Appalachians\"},{\"insert\":\"). West Virginia is bordered by five states, on the south and east by \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Virginia\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Virginia\"},{\"insert\":\", \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Maryland\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Maryland\"},{\"insert\":\" to the north and east, the north by \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Pennsylvania\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Pennsylvania\"},{\"insert\":\", the north and west by \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Ohio\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Ohio\"},{\"insert\":\" and \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Kentucky\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\"},\"insert\":\"Kentucky\"},{\"insert\":\" to the west.\\n\\nOriginally part of the state of Virginia, the residents of the counties that became West Virginia split from the rest of the state in part due to a disagreement over the issues of slavery and secession. These counties elected to remain with the Union during the \"},{