texas_body = "{\"ops\":[{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"http://www.traveltex.com/\",\"bold\":true,\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"Texas\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\" is the second largest and second most populous state in the \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/United_States_of_America\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"United States of America\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\". Owing to its remarkable size, distinctive culture and politics, and colorful history, many Texans maintain a fiercely independent attitude, with Texan identity often superseding American identity. Few other American states feature their flag so prominently in businesses, on the backs of cars and in advertisements. Originally a territory of \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Spain\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"Spain\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\" and, later, \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Mexico\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"Mexico\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\", Texas rebelled in 1836 and became its own nation for 10 years before being annexed by the United States in 1845. Despite having existed under the auspices of six different nations (\"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/France\",\"color\":\"rgb(11, 0, 128)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\"France\"},{\"attributes\":{\"color\":\"rgb(37, 37, 37)\",\"font\":\"sans-serif\",\"size\":\"14px\"},\"insert\":\", Spain, Mexico, the Republic of Texas, the United States of America, and the Confederate States of America), Texas has maintained its fascinating independent spirit, making for a unique and unrivaled exploration ground for any intrigued and intrepid adventurer.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"http://garyrash.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Texas-Road.jpg\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"}]}"
Note.create(title: "Texas", body: texas_body, author_id: 1, notebook_id: 3)

